<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1111,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1111,1137]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head black dorsally, antennomeres VI and VII lobate; ventral surface yellow; mouthparts and coxae brown. Pronotum with wide lateral margins, pronotum and elytron brown. Elytron yellow with brown maculae and fasciae; two lateral maculae near apex, sutural fascia continuous reaching the base, with a large brown macula on the disc, lateral fascia discontinuous, joining with discal macula near apex (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1348,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
a). Last abdominal ventrite smooth with distinct edge (
<figureCitation box="[733,811,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
b). Aedeagus with wide and bifid base, apical half gradually narrowed, apex truncate but widened laterally (
<figureCitation box="[833,910,1298,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Figs 4</figureCitation>
c–e). Paramere, in dorsal view, with internal edge undulate, converging near base and with rows of setae rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1147,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
c); in ventral view, basal half large joining to other side, apical half thin with apex rounded with setae (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1133,1373,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1111,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,351,1410,1436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[360,471,1410,1436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Holotype</typeStatus>
male: total length 1.44 mm; maximum width 0.96 mm; elytral length 0.77 mm; maximum width of pronotum 0.96 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1111,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
Body rounded. Head inconspicuously punctate; clypeus indistinctly beaded; antennae with round scape, pedicel narrower and longer than flagellomeres, antennomeres VI and VII lobate. Pronotum short and wide, very fine and inconspicuously punctate, wide lateral margins; prosternal process small and setiforme; metasternum, metacoxae and abdomen with small, scattered, fine punctures. Tarsi pentamerous without modifications. Elytron very fine and obscurely punctated. Last abdominal ventrite smooth with distinct edge (
<figureCitation box="[159,231,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
b). Aedeagus with base wide and bifid and apical half gradually narrowed, apex truncated but widened laterally (
<figureCitation box="[262,338,1709,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Figs 4</figureCitation>
c–e). Parameres, in dorsal view, with internal edge undulating, converging near base and with rows of setae at apex (
<figureCitation box="[413,485,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
c); in ventral view with basal half large joining to other side, apical half thin with apex rounded, with setae (
<figureCitation box="[458,530,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1111,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,339,1821,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head black dorsally. Pronotum yellow with black base. Elytron yellow with brown maculae and fasciae; two lateral maculae near apex, sutural fascia continuous, reaching the base, with a large brown macula on the disc, lateral fascia discontinuous, joining with discal macula near apex (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1309,1896,1922]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[238,1357,185,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[238,1357,175,1814]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3) Desmopachria cavia sp. nov. 4) D. nigrocapitata sp. nov. a) Dorsal habitus; b) last visible abdominal ventrite; c) male genitalia, dorsal view; d) male genitalia, ventral view; e) male genitalia, dorsal view with cover slips. Scale in dorsal habitus = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204764/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
a). Ventral surface yellow; mouthparts and coxae brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1111,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,325,1970,1996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">Variation.</emphasis>
The size of the body is not variable. Small variation in the position of the lateral spots and fasciae.
</paragraph>
